WRITING.TEXT: Hey, Thank you! You can easily record 70 minutes without interruption. Then the battery is almost empty. It probably also depends on the settings. Yes, that's true! I use the desktop version of the app from Insta360 Insta Studio. From there I export the videos. There is a plug-in for Adobe Premiere Pro. There you can open the Insta files directly. With the new update, you can also save the files as mp4. Not this strange Insta format anymore. But then the whole thing is without the stabilization etc. But maybe there are other aways. I still don't know enough about the camera and video editing in general. I never had problems with overheating. I often record without interruption until the battery is empty. When I film in very high resolution over 4k 30 fps it comes to image shaking in places. But I think it is because of the memory card. It cannot write fast enough. But all in all I like the camera. But as I said, I don't know much about the camera yet. And also not with filming and video. I am still trying it out. I hope I could help you a little bit anyway. Maybe someone else can tell you more about it here - share their experiences? P.S Poste, if you want the link to your channel. Then I can also subscribe to you.
